    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't that kind of a slippery slope? if the state starts deciding which religious beliefs are \"valid\" enough to qualify for an exception and which ones aren't, aren't they basically just imposing their own secular worldview on everyone else? feels like that's actually more dangerous for democracy than just having a few exceptions.",
