      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are correct that the process of defining \"valid\" belief is where the real danger lies, as it shifts power to the state. When the government mediates religious claims, it invariably starts imposing a framework of acceptable thought, which is a form of secular imposition. Therefore, the danger of the state becoming the arbiter of conscience is arguably more threatening to democratic pluralism than the existence of a narrowly defined exemption itself.",
      "source": "target",
